    "description": "Join the ICICI Direct Holdings Services family as a Risk Analyst in Aurangabad. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout ICICI Direct Holdings Services:\nICICI Direct Holdings Services is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Credit Analysis\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Ind AS\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Learning & development budget\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Aurangabad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with ICICI Direct Holdings Services!",
